# Getting started with SendinBlue

To use any of the above modules, you need to connect your SendinBlue account to Integromat. If you do not have a SendinBlue account yet, you can create one at [sendinblue.com](https://www.sendinblue.com/users/login/).

## Connecting the SendinBlue service to Integromat

To connect your SendinBlue account to Integromat, follow the general instructions for [Connecting to services](https://support.integromat.com/hc/en-us/articles/360001990194#create-a-connection). 

![](https://integromat.zendesk.com/hc/article_attachments/360009138694/file.png)

![](https://integromat.zendesk.com/hc/article_attachments/360009138714/file.png)

After clicking on the **Add** button, another window will open which will require you to type an API key. To get the API key, log into your SendinBlue account and in the top right corner, click on your profile icon and select **SMTP & API**.

![](https://integromat.zendesk.com/hc/article_attachments/360009138734/file.png)

![](https://integromat.zendesk.com/hc/article_attachments/360009184153/file.png)

Copy the displayed key and paste it into the **API key** field in Integromat. After that click on the **Save** button.

Next, select the **Event type** and **Events** you want to be notified of, and click on the **Save** button once again.

![](https://integromat.zendesk.com/hc/article_attachments/360009138774/file.png)

This will create a webhook which will allow Integromat to receive a notification when a specified event occurs in SendinBlue. The URL address that Integromat listens to for the event will be automatically registered with SendinBlue, you don't have to enter it manually.

![](https://integromat.zendesk.com/hc/article_attachments/360009138794/file.png)

Now you can continue and finish your scenario.

options.label: request (emails sent by Sendinblue SMTP)
delivered (delivered emails)
hard bounce (emails which were not delivered and which will never arrive at destination)
soft bounce (emails which were not temporarily delivered)
blocked (spam report emails + hard bounce emails when they are repeated)
spam (when a person who received your email reported that it is a spam)
invalid email (if a ISP again indicated us that the email is not valid)
deferred (these are emails which are not sent because of temporary failure)
opened (when a person who received your email, opens it)
click (when a person clicks any link in email received)
unsubscribe (when a person unsubscribes from the email received)
unique opened (when an email received by a person is uniquely opened)
